          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f \colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> have a <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000X.xml" title="Quasi-inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-inverse</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> with incoherent counit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon \colon  f\circ  g\sim  1_{B}]]></fr:tex> and unit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta \colon  g\circ  f\sim  1_{A}]]></fr:tex>. We can <html:em>correct</html:em> the counit to obtain a coherent <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000W.xml" title="Inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000W" type="local">inverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>30</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-002C/0</fr:addr><fr:route>http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002C/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>The corrected counit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon ' \colon  g\circ  f\sim  1_{A}]]></fr:tex> is defined like so:</html:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \epsilon ' x :\equiv 
  \epsilon 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
^{-1} \cdot  \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \eta 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 \cdot  \epsilon  x
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>The coherence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ  \eta  \sim  \epsilon '\circ  f]]></fr:tex> can be constructed using our two naturality lemmas <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001V.xml" title="Naturality of homotopies" addr="forest://erct/erct-001V" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001V" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001W.xml" title="Naturality of homotopies onto the identity" addr="forest://erct/erct-001W" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001W" /></fr:link>.</html:p>
