            <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-001W</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001W.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Naturality of homotopies onto the identity">Naturality of <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0014.xml" title="Homotopy" addr="forest://erct/erct-0014" type="local">homotopies</fr:link> onto the identity</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001W.agda" type="external">erct-001W.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H \colon  f \sim  1_{A}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0014.xml" title="Homotopy" addr="forest://erct/erct-0014" type="local">homotopy</fr:link> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  A]]></fr:tex> onto the identity function. Then we may construct a higher homotopy from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H\circ  f]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}\circ  H]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>21</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-001W/0</fr:addr><fr:route>http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001W/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>Fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex>, we must construct an identification from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>. By the naturality (<fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001V.xml" title="Naturality of homotopies" addr="forest://erct/erct-001V" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001V" /></fr:link>) of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> at the identification <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H x\colon  f x = x]]></fr:tex>, we have an identification <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 \cdot  \mathsf {act}_{1_{A}}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cdot  H x]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 <html:p>Simplifying, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cdot  H x = \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cdot  H x]]></fr:tex>; canceling <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H x]]></fr:tex> on either side, we therefore have the desired identification <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
